<br>
1. WAR 9400/9945 (-545)<br>
2. WIZ 6200/6200<br>
3. CLR 6500/6500<br>
4. WAR 9220/9865 (-645)<br>
5. RNG 7250/8100 (-850)<br>
6. DRU 7000/7000<br>
<br>
Figure in the total damage taken throughout the group...<br>
<br>
= 2040<br>
<br>
Now, figure out the average damage per group member...<br>
<br>
= 2040/6 = 340<br>
<br>
Distribute that damage evenly throughout the group now...<br>
<br>
1. WAR 9605/9945 (-205) (+340)<br>
2. WIZ 5860/6200 (-340)<br>
3. CLR 6160/6500 (-340)<br>
4. WAR 9525/9865 (-305) (+340)<br>
5. RNG 7760/8100 (-340) (+510)<br>
6. DRU 6660/7000 (-340)<br>
<br>
Hope that makes sense. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fredre@graffeswizardcompilation>Fredre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 653<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/30/03 12:16 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Straight melee types would thrown a monkey into the works.  Maybe somehow ignore them would be best.<br>
